          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-06-29T21:00:07Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Honoring Hometown Heroes Act</strong></p> <p>This bill authorizes the governor of a state, territory, or possession of the United States or the Mayor of the District of Columbia to proclaim that the U.S. flag shall be flown at half-staff in the event of the death of a first responder (public safety officer) working in such jurisdiction who dies while serving in the line of duty.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2016-06-14T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
